    h2 Bio
    p.
        Kim has been a developer at the University of Minnesota for over 14 years working on projects big and small. 
        Until recently changing over to full-stack Nodejs development, her main technical roles included UX design, building accessible UIs and font end development.

    p.
        She also has a background in instructional design, project management, and business analysis.  She taught at both the high school (physics), professional (instructional design) and college level (web design) but her favorite task was to introduce preschoolers to computer programming. 
        She is a University of Minnesota graduate with undergraduate degrees in physics and astronomy (with additional emphasis on chemistry and history of science) and completed advanced coursework in curriculum and instruction along with instructional design for online learning.

